tions\" say \"Fix this issues\" and list specific failures, I should:\n1. Investigate whether the current selectors are actually fixing the issues\n2. Potentially explore the live site to validate selectors\n3. Generate the report based on the provided failure data\n\nFor the newsletter (TC-83232): The selector `div.bg-primary input[type=\"email\"]` - need to verify if this matches the live DOM\nFor TC-83240: LoginPage already uses `/auth/login` - the error was at `LoginPage.ts:28` which was the old `/myaccount` version\nFor TC-83238: Already has robust handling\n\nLet me check if the current test code at home-page.spec.ts around line 414 matches what was failing. The error shows:\n```\n412 |     // element to mount before interacting.\n413 |     await page.evaluate(() => window.scrollTo(0, document.body.scrollHeight));\n414 |     await homePage.newsletterEmailInput.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 30_000 });\n```\n\nBut in the current file at line 478: `await homePage.newsletterEmailInput.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 45_000 });`\n\nThis confirms the current code already has a different implementation. The error was from an older version. \n\n**BUT** the selector `div.bg-primary input[type=\"email\"]` is still the same. The issue might be:\n1. Timeout (old: 30s, new: 45s) — already fixed\n2. Selector wrong — may still be wrong\n3. Scroll strategy — already improved\n\nThe root cause could be the selector if the newsletter section renders inside a different container on the live site.\n\nGiven the context, I should:\n1. Use the browser to check the newsletter form selector on the UAT\n2. Fix if needed\n3. Generate the report\n\nActually, looking at the error more carefully: all 3 types of failure share a common trait - they're all **locator not found within timeout** issues. The current code has already increased timeouts and improved scroll strategies. The underlying selector `div.bg-primary input[type=\"email\"]` for newsletter might be the real issue.\